<subsection xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="subsec-additive-and-multiplicative-inverses">
<title>Additive and multiplicative inverses</title>
<p>Let z = <em>x</em>+i<em>y</em> be a complex number, then</p>
<p>
    <ol marker="i)">
        <li>
            <p>
                its additive inverse denoted by <m>(- z )</m> is given by : <m>-z = - ( x + iy) = - x - iy</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                its multiplicative inverse denoted by <m>z ^{-1}</m> is given by : <m>z^{-1} = \frac{1}{x + iy} = \frac{x}{x^{2} + y^{2}} - \frac{iy}{x^{2} + y^{2}}</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</p>
<example>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Find the additive and multiplicative inverses of the complex number <m>z = 3 + 4i</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
        <p>
            <m>z = 3 + 4i</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>i) -z = -3 - 4i</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>ii) z^{-1} = \frac{1}{3 + 4i} = \frac{1}{3 + 4i} \cdot \frac{3 - 4i}{3 - 4i} = \frac{3}{25} - \frac{4i}{25}</m>.
        </p>
    </solution>
</example>

